snippet.textDisplay:
What young people don't realise is that even just a caution will be on their record forever along with their finger prints, photos and dna. It will affect their ability to travel, to apply for credit, to get a job...everything. For tourists, its a one way ticket to immigration detention or remand prison and a ticket home at their expense, plus a future travel ban. Its just not worh it.
Do not come here to commit a crime. The cops are a cut above your usual beat cops here, are highly trained and relentless about street crime. There are more undercover cops in tourist hotspots than you imagine. In the Bondi Local Command there are over 300 police. Theft is in the category of a violent crime. There is no probable cause limitation on arrest, nor do you have an indefinite right to silence. You also do not have an automatic right to a free lawyer. It might take three months to get one allocated. In the meantime you will be jailed on remand. If you are an illegal immigrant you go to detention until you are dealt with, even for those claiming asylum. You are not released into the community like in the UK.
